    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Frans van Cranevelt to Miklós Oláh (Mechelen, 28 April
                    1537)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">He wants to see Oláh’s <hi rend="italic">Hungaria</hi>
                            in person as well, but it has not happened yet. He is hawking his cento
                            poems onto Oláh, which Nanninck liked so much that he is pushing for
                            their publication. He is sending it to Oláh for review: if he likes it,
                            it can be forwarded to Nanninck, if he does not, he will destroy it.
                        </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/401AD960-04FA-4525-B284-8E368F060AD6
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Idem Nicolao Olao salutem plurimam. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Cupio iampridem occasionem mihi dari istuc proficiscendi, ut <hi
                        rend="italic">Hungariam</hi> tuam videre liceat, sed hactenus fortuna nobis
                    id genus voluptatis invidit. Ego vero tibi meas nugas obtrudo, nisi potius
                    dicendum sit nec meas esse. Quippe <milestone unit="pb" facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/794BB3BE-641D-44D4-A139-3AF38A470315
                        "/>qui alienis opibus
                    abusus sum et Claudiani<note xml:id="note.1">Claudius Claudianus (370–404),
                        Roman poet.</note> labores in rem meam verterim, centonem consarcinavi, sed
                    non his legibus, quibus olim veteres et quibus <persName>Ausonius</persName> in
                    suo Virgilio centone<note xml:id="note.2"><hi rend="italic">Cento
                            nuptialis.</hi></note> sit usus. Ita tamen placuit viro doctissimo ac
                    communi amico domino <persName>Petro Nannio</persName>,<note xml:id="note.3"
                        >Pieter Nanninck.</note> ut me vehementer urgeat ad edendum. Mitto tibi
                    opusculum ipsum cum illius epistolio, ut Dominatio Tua iudicet, quid mihi
                    faciendum sit. <del corresp="Olahus">Promitto</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                        type="corr">Permitto</add> tibi liberam statuendi facultatem, ut si edendum
                    videatur, recta via mittatur ad <persName>Nannium</persName>, sin minus, tum
                    quod ille dicebat <quote xml:id="quote.1">de Apiace<note xml:id="note.4">I.e.
                            Aiace.</note> caesar noster: <del corresp="Olahus">concumbet</del><add
                            corresp="Olahus" type="corr">incumbet</add> in spongeam.</quote><note
                        type="quote" xml:id="note.quote.1">Suet. <hi rend="italic">De vitis
                            caesarum,</hi> Div. Aug. 85: “respondit, Aiacem suum in spongeam
                        incubuisse”.</note> Vale, Vir Ornatissime et Cranneveldium tuum, quod <del
                        corresp="Olahus">facit</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">facis</add>,
                    ama. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3"><placeName>Mechliniae</placeName> quarto Kalendas Maias anno
                    1537.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
